Dear Hiring Team,

I am writing to apply for the *Software Engineer* role with *Bamboo Health*. I bring over three years of experience building backend systems, workflow automation, and AI-assisted tooling, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Across Sperse and Qualitest, I have built production software that maps closely to the technical depth this position demands. At Sperse, I designed a *customer-facing* *multi-agent* CRM platform in *Python*, *FastAPI*, *LangGraph*, and *LangChain* that served 10,000+ users by routing requests across 40+ specialized sub-agents with secure access control and tenant-aware JWT propagation. I also shipped a *React Flow* and *TypeScript* workflow builder with *Temporal* durable execution, and built an *OpenAI Codex*-powered code review pipeline with a custom Bitbucket MCP server that automated 25-30 PRs/week. To keep those releases reliable, I paired OpenTelemetry trace-driven evals with GitHub Actions *CI/CD* gates and unit and functional test checks, which maps directly to Bamboo Health’s emphasis on performant, secure, scalable delivery and strong engineering discipline.

At Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in *Java* and *Spring Boot* backed by *PostgreSQL*, *Redis*, and *SQL* that handled uploads, downloads, and deletions across *AWS S3*, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO through expiring signed URLs. I also optimized relational queries with window functions, materialized views, and indexes, then exposed the data through interactive *React* visualizations for business stakeholders. Finally, I orchestrated long-running jobs with *AWS Step Functions* to eliminate *AWS Lambda* timeouts and improve error recovery across *100K+* weekly executions. That experience gave me the systems-level thinking, database fluency, and operational focus needed to contribute meaningfully to Bamboo Health’s customer-facing applications and services.

Bamboo Health’s mission to empower clients to deliver seamless, high-quality, and cost-effective care during pivotal moments to improve health outcomes resonates with me, as does the company’s focus on improving care and outcomes and improving provider and patient experience. I would welcome the opportunity to bring that mindset, along with my experience in *Java*, *Spring Boot*, *AWS Lambda*, *SQL*, and AI-assisted development tools, to a team building Real-Time Care Intelligence™ for the moments that matter most.

I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

